As controversies rage on in the wake of the murder of Super TV CEO Usifo Ataga at a Lekki, Lagos Short Service apartment by his 21-year-old lover Chidinma Ojukwu on June 15, photos of the crime scene are now available thanks to TVC
The National Daily reported how family and friends insisted Ataga was no womanizer, and that he might have been assassinated.

Ojukwu, a 300-level mass communication student at UNILAG, confessed to killing the man after they were both drugged up, and Ataga wanted more sex forcibly.
Recovered from the scene are: Ataga’s car, photos of blood-stained beddings, floor, and others.

